divs: Sighting DetailsBecause of the many accounts of people finding anomolous stuff in pictures that they didn't see with the naked eye, I will occasionally take random pictures of the sky and examine them on my computer. The very first time I did this back in 2005 I got a picture of 3 white lights in broad daylight. On November 7th, 2011 I was in my backyard (Baytown, TX) and took 2 pictures of the sky approx. 3 seconds apart. I did not see anything with the naked eye at the time. After uploading them to my computer, I opened them with a Photoshop-type program so I could examine them closer. Initially, I did not see anything (in the original picture, the object is only VERY faintly visible.) I know that simply adjusting the brightness and contrast of a photo can greatly enhance the visibility of things. I did this and immediately saw a curious dark line in the clouds in the first picture. So I used a few more techniques to enhance the photo further (sharpened it, negative filter, etc.) I was shocked at what became visible! It looks like a cigar-shaped object (or a disk-shape viewed from the side) with what appear to be dark "windows." I am attaching the original photo along with the enhanced ones. The object was not in the second picture taken almost immediately after.
